## 2. Persistent State (on all servers)

These MUST be persisted to stable storage (disk) before responding to any RPC. If you lose these on crash, safety is violated.

| Variable | Type | Initial Value | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `currentTerm` | integer | 0 | The latest term this server has seen. Increases monotonically. |
| `votedFor` | server ID or null | null | The candidateId that this server voted for in the current term, or null if it hasn't voted. |
| `log[]` | array of log entries | empty | Each entry contains: `command` (the state machine command), `term` (the term when the entry was received by the leader). Log is 1-indexed. |

**Critical**: `currentTerm` and `votedFor` must be updated atomically on disk before sending any RPC response. Failure to persist these before responding can violate the "at most one leader per term" safety property.

