## 3. Volatile State

### 3.1 On All Servers

| Variable | Type | Initial Value | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `commitIndex` | integer | 0 | Index of the highest log entry known to be committed. Increases monotonically. |
| `lastApplied` | integer | 0 | Index of the highest log entry applied to the state machine. Increases monotonically. |

### 3.2 On Leaders Only (reinitialized after each election)

| Variable | Type | Initial Value | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `nextIndex[]` | array of integers | leader's last log index + 1 (for each server) | For each server, the index of the next log entry to send to that server. |
| `matchIndex[]` | array of integers | 0 (for each server) | For each server, the index of the highest log entry known to be replicated on that server. Increases monotonically. |

